summary: I am highly motivated by any new and innovative technology, and I use my creativity in every task that must be accomplished. I am now specializing in the field of Computational (Bio)mechanics, Finite Element Analysis, Mathematical Modeling and Biomedical Engineering. I want to continue expanding my knowledge in these fields and gain more experience and development to become more competitive as an Engineer.

projects: [{'title': 'Master of Science Thesis - "A Computational Study of Combination Therapies in Growing Tumors: Combination of Chemotherapy and Radiotherapy"', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}, 'end': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2023}}, 'description': 'My master of science thesis deals with the computational study of combination therapies in growing tumors, especially the combination of chemotherapy and radiotherapy. To carry out this computational study, a two‑dimensional, continuous mathematical model was developed and solved in the environment of COMSOL Multiphysics ®. In the model mentioned above, radiotherapy and chemotherapy were applied to observe how these treatments affect the number of cancer cells and the number of blood vessels connected to these cancer cells.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Marina', 'last_name': 'Koutsi', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Computational Mechanics (NTUA), Materials Science Engineer (UOI)'}]}, {'title': 'Diploma thesis - “Computational study of the change of the mechanical environment of the fractured bone for different geometrical characteristics of bone callus."', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2017}, 'end': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': 'My thesis examines the numerical evaluation of the healing progression in long bones with the help of an external fixation device using the finite element method (FEM) applied in the Ansys tool. For this purpose, a three‑dimensional (3D) model of the femur bone was developed to study the total deformation of bone and external fixation device, for every stage of the healing process, under the load corresponding to a gait cycle.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Marina', 'last_name': 'Koutsi', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Computational Mechanics (NTUA), Materials Science Engineer (UOI)'}]}]
